  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Success rate of reversal maneuvers to restore signal above the threshold</measure>
    <time_frame>Intraoperative</time_frame>
    <description>Number and type of maneuver(s) in response to an alert&#xD;
number and type of successful maneuvers&#xD;
number and type of unsuccessful maneuvers</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Neurological status</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline up to 30 days postoperative</time_frame>
    <description>Neurological status:&#xD;
• ASIA Lower extremity motor and sensory score including if a spinal cord syndrome is applicable. A scale from 0 to 5 points in which 0 denotes total paralysis and 5 normal active movement. Sensory will be meassured as either normal, altered or absent.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
